EARNINGS 
Michael I. Cohen and Richard P. Kuntz have joined 3i Capital, Newport Beach, as 
vice presidents. The firm invests in companies seeking capital for growth, the 
repurchase of shares or leveraged buyouts. Cohen was previously an investment 
manager with Norwest Venture Capital in Portland. Before that, he served in 
engineering and management positions with General Electric Co. in Philadelphia 
and Kulicke &amp; Soffa Industries Inc. in Horsham, Pa. Kuntz had previously 
been vice president, corporate finance, for Prudential Capital Corp., a 
subsidiary of Prudential Insurance Co. of America. Earlier, he held analytical 
and operating positions with E.F. Hutton &amp; Co., New York, and Texas Air 
Corp., Houston. 
